      "text": "Operational questions:\n- Does our **Keycloak machinery** support this transparently and reliably? Is it production-ready?\n- Do we need a **staffed location** aka helpdesk/front office, where the manual processes are carried out, and members are entered into a registry and issued with credentials? Do we intend to automate this from the start? Maybe SSO?\n- Do we have standard subscription rates (eg a **basic individual account**, with a defined *maximum of sites* and a defined *envelope of functionality aka plugins*) which can be advertised and accessed in OpenCollective?\n- Are we ready to advertise individual (and organisational) accounts in wiki.cafe? Or is this still alpha development status (like RelocalizeCreativity)? Where do we advertise accounts: OC? Our own website (where is this)? Who maintains this - an *operational role* question for a **Product circle** within the wiki.cafe organisation. Is it time to create this circle, as distinct from the sysadmin traffic? I’ve created a room in our matrix space, and the wiki xxx to support this circle."
